{
  "chapter": {
    "children": [
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "1",
            "text": "By the rivers of Babylon"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "we sat down and wept"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "when we thought about Zion."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "2",
            "text": "On the poplars there"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "we hung our harps."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "3",
            "text": "There our captors required songs from us,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "and those who mocked us required us to be happy, saying,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "“Sing us one of the songs of Zion.”"
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "4",
            "text": "How could we sing a song about Yahweh"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "in a foreign land?"
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "5",
            "text": "If I ignore the memory of you, Jerusalem,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "let my right hand forget her skill."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "6",
            "text": "Let my tongue cling to the roof of my mouth"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "if I think about you no more,"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "if I do not prefer Jerusalem"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "more than my greatest delights."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "7",
            "text": "Call to mind, Yahweh, what the Edomites did"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "on the day Jerusalem fell."
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "They said, “Tear it down, tear it down"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "to its foundations.”"
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "8",
            "text": "Daughter of Babylon, soon to be destroyed—"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "may the person be blessed, whoever pays you back"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "for what you have done to us."
          },
          {
            "tag": "v",
            "num": "9",
            "text": "May the person be blessed, whoever takes and dashes your little ones"
          },
          {
            "tag": "q",
            "text": "against a rock."
          }
        ],
        "tag": "m"
      }
    ],
    "num": 137
  },
